# Docker build-context exclusions.
#
# Without this file, `docker build` (and `docker compose up --build`) uploads
# the ENTIRE repo directory to the build daemon, even though the Dockerfiles
# only need a handful of source files. With the SQLite chain index and the
# nightly backup snapshots living in the repo, that "entire repo" can run to
# 15+ GB — every rebuild waits minutes just to transfer junk that's about to
# be ignored.
#
# Keep this list in sync with Dockerfile.backend (which COPYs server.js + db.js
# only) and Dockerfile.frontend (which COPYs the whole tree, hence relies on
# this exclusion list to filter out the heavy stuff).

# ─── Runtime data — never belongs in a built image ──────────────────────────
# The SQLite chain index lives here when DATA_PATH defaults to ./data. Bind-
# mounted into the container at runtime via docker-compose.yml, so excluding
# it from the build context doesn't break anything; the volume mount supplies
# the same files.
data/

# Nightly backup archives written by backup.sh. Big and tarball-like.
backups/
*.db
*.db.gz
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-wal
*.sqlite-shm

# ─── Dependencies & build artefacts ─────────────────────────────────────────
# node_modules is reinstalled INSIDE the image — sending the host copy bloats
# the context and risks injecting a glibc-linked binary into an alpine image.
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# Vite output goes here at build time; rebuilt inside the image.
dist/
.vite/

# ─── Caches & temp ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cache JSON files written by server.js (cold-start fallbacks). Each is < 1 MB
# but they get refreshed at runtime anyway.
*_cache.json
*.log

# Scratchpad / generator outputs that aren't part of the deployable image.
outputs/

# ─── Version control + editor metadata ──────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ─── Environment & secrets ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The container reads .env via env_file in docker-compose; baking it into the
# image is a leak vector.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# ─── Local-only docs that don't need to ship in the image ───────────────────
# These exist for repo readers but the running container doesn't use them.
README.md
SECURITY_AUDIT.md
BRAND.md
CLAUDE.md
*.pdf

# ─── Letsencrypt artefacts (bind-mounted, not built in) ─────────────────────
certbot/

# ─── Misc ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Useful catch-all for editors that drop tilde backups.
*~

# NOTE: We DON'T exclude Dockerfile.* or docker-compose*.yml here — Docker
# reads them out of the context, and excluding them can break `docker compose
# build` depending on the invocation. They're tiny anyway.
